				\begin{document}$$ \frac{di_L}{dt}=\frac{v_L}{L}=\frac{v_{in}-{v}_o}{L},t\in \left[0, Dt\right] $$\end{document}

During this period inductor L is charging. At time t = t1, switch M1 opens and the energy stored in the inductor is delivered to the load through diode D which becomes forward biased. The inductor is now discharging and IL decreases at the rate of.6diLdt=vLL=−voL,t∈DtT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
